                "content": "**Nervous System** = the body's electrical communication network that coordinates responses to stimuli.\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- Receive information from receptors (sensory input)\n- Process and interpret information (integration)\n- Send commands to effectors (motor output)\n- Coordinate voluntary and involuntary responses\n- Enable consciousness, memory, learning, emotions\n\n**Why electrical signals?**\nThe nervous system uses ELECTRICAL impulses (nerve signals) traveling along neurons. This is MUCH faster than chemical signals (hormones in blood).\n\n**Speed comparison:**\n- Nerve signal: 0.1-120 meters per second (up to 430 km/h!)\n- Hormone in blood: ~0.5 meters per second (walking pace)\n\nWhen you need a response in milliseconds (pulling hand from fire), you need electrical speed!",
